{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":991,"text":"When I was four years old,"},{"time":2687,"text":"my dad taught me\nthe Taos Pueblo Hoop Dance,"},{"time":5606,"text":"a traditional dance born hundreds\nof years ago in Southwestern USA."},{"time":10508,"text":"A series of hoops are created\nout of willow wood,"},{"time":13452,"text":"and they're threaded together\nto create formations of the natural world,"},{"time":17338,"text":"showing the many beauties of life."},{"time":19923,"text":"In this dance, you're circling\nin a constant spin,"},{"time":22929,"text":"mimicking the movement of the Sun"},{"time":25015,"text":"and the passage of time."},{"time":28232,"text":"Watching this dance was magic to me."},{"time":31515,"text":"Like with a time capsule,"},{"time":32897,"text":"I was taking a look through\na cultural window to the past."},{"time":36201,"text":"I felt a deeper connection"},{"time":38133,"text":"to how my ancestors used to look\nat the world around them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42046,"text":"Since then, I've always been\nobsessed with time capsules."},{"time":45819,"text":"They take on many forms,"},{"time":47471,"text":"but the common thread\nis that they're uncontrollably fascinating"},{"time":50580,"text":"to us as human beings,"},{"time":52726,"text":"because they're portals to a memory,"},{"time":54916,"text":"and they hold the important power\nof keeping stories alive."},{"time":59503,"text":"As a filmmaker and composer,"},{"time":61636,"text":"it's been my journey to find my voice,"},{"time":64239,"text":"reclaim the stories\nof my heritage and the past"},{"time":67632,"text":"and infuse them into music and film\ntime capsules to share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72838,"text":"To tell you a bit about\nhow I found my voice,"},{"time":75188,"text":"I'd like to share a bit\nabout how I grew up."},{"time":77880,"text":"In Southern California, I grew up\nin a multigenerational home,"},{"time":81296,"text":"meaning I lived under the same roof"},{"time":83210,"text":"as my parents, aunts,\nuncles and grandparents."},{"time":86936,"text":"My mother is Dutch-Indonesian and Chinese\nwith immigrant parents,"},{"time":91583,"text":"and my father is Ojibwe"},{"time":93593,"text":"and an enrolled tribal member"},{"time":95221,"text":"of the Prairie Band's Potawatomi Tribe\nin Northeastern Kansas."},{"time":99238,"text":"So one weekend I'd be learning\nhow to fold dumplings,"},{"time":102242,"text":"and the next, I'd be\ntraditional-style dancing"},{"time":104571,"text":"at a powwow,"},{"time":105792,"text":"immersed in the powerful sounds\nof drums and singers."},{"time":110405,"text":"Being surrounded by many\ncultures was the norm,"},{"time":113035,"text":"but also a very confusing experience."},{"time":116500,"text":"It was really hard for me\nto find my voice,"},{"time":118713,"text":"because I never felt I was enough --"},{"time":120979,"text":"never Chinese, Dutch-Indonesian\nor Native enough."},{"time":125381,"text":"Because I never felt I was a part\nof any community,"},{"time":128456,"text":"I sought to learn\nthe stories of my heritage"},{"time":131913,"text":"and connect them together\nto rediscover my own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135254,"text":"The first medium I felt\ngave me a voice was music."},{"time":140043,"text":"With layers of sounds\nand multiple instruments,"},{"time":143249,"text":"I could create soundscapes and worlds\nthat were much bigger than my own."},{"time":147556,"text":"Through music, I'm inviting you\ninto a sonic portal"},{"time":150460,"text":"of my memories and emotions,"},{"time":152486,"text":"and I'm holding up a mirror to yours."},{"time":155538,"text":"One of my favorite instruments to play\nis the guzheng zither,"},{"time":158762,"text":"a Chinese harp-like instrument."},{"time":161190,"text":"While the hoop dance\nis hundreds of years old,"},{"time":163518,"text":"the guzheng has more\nthan 2,000 years of history."},{"time":167337,"text":"I'm playing the styles that greatly\ninfluence me today,"},{"time":170036,"text":"like electronic music,"},{"time":171697,"text":"with an instrument that was used\nto play traditional folk music long ago."},{"time":176235,"text":"And I noticed an interesting connection:"},{"time":179077,"text":"the zither is tuned\nto the pentatonic scale,"},{"time":181532,"text":"a scale that is universally known\nin so many parts of music"},{"time":185108,"text":"around the world,"},{"time":186317,"text":"including Native American folk songs."},{"time":189781,"text":"In both Chinese and Native folk,"},{"time":191727,"text":"I sense this inherent sound of longing\nand holding onto the past,"},{"time":196008,"text":"an emotion that greatly drives\nthe music I create today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200603,"text":"At the time, I wondered if I could make\nthis feeling of immersion"},{"time":204165,"text":"even more powerful,"},{"time":205347,"text":"by layering visuals and music --"},{"time":207583,"text":"visuals and images on top of the music."},{"time":210870,"text":"So I turned to internet tutorials\nto learn editing software,"},{"time":214472,"text":"went to community college to save money"},{"time":216593,"text":"and created films."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219012,"text":"After a few years experimenting,"},{"time":220775,"text":"I was 17 and had something\nI wanted to tell and preserve."},{"time":224197,"text":"It started with a question:"},{"time":226692,"text":"What happens when a story is forgotten?"},{"time":230985,"text":"I lead with this in my latest\ndocumentary film,"},{"time":233679,"text":"\"Smoke That Travels,\""},{"time":235220,"text":"which immerses people into the world\nof music, song, color and dance,"},{"time":240529,"text":"as I explore my fear that a part\nof my identity, my Native heritage,"},{"time":245865,"text":"will be forgotten in time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248728,"text":"Many indigenous languages are dying\ndue to historically forced assimilation."},{"time":253619,"text":"From the late 1800s to the early 1970s,"},{"time":257261,"text":"Natives were forced into boarding schools,"},{"time":259720,"text":"where they were violently punished\nif they practiced traditional ways"},{"time":263340,"text":"or spoke their native language,"},{"time":265086,"text":"most of which were orally passed down."},{"time":267892,"text":"As of now, there are 567 federally\nrecognized tribes in the United States,"},{"time":273591,"text":"when there used to be countless more."},{"time":276179,"text":"In my father's words,"},{"time":277803,"text":"\"Being Native is not about\nwearing long hair in braids."},{"time":281386,"text":"It's not about feathers or beadwork."},{"time":284244,"text":"It's about the way we all center ourselves\nin the world as human beings.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":289776,"text":"After traveling with this film\nfor over a year,"},{"time":292099,"text":"I met indigenous people\nfrom around the world,"},{"time":294524,"text":"from the Ainu of Japan,"},{"time":296177,"text":"Sami of Scandinavia,"},{"time":297651,"text":"the Maori"},{"time":298850,"text":"and many more."},{"time":300108,"text":"And they were all dealing\nwith the exact same struggle"},{"time":303991,"text":"to preserve their language and culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307168,"text":"At this moment, I not only realize\nthe power storytelling has"},{"time":310782,"text":"to connect all of us as human beings"},{"time":313198,"text":"but the responsibility\nthat comes with this power."},{"time":316480,"text":"It can become incredibly dangerous\nwhen our stories are rewritten or ignored,"},{"time":320802,"text":"because when we are denied identity,"},{"time":322812,"text":"we become invisible."},{"time":324890,"text":"We're all storytellers."},{"time":327705,"text":"Reclaiming our narratives\nand just listening to each other's"},{"time":332365,"text":"can create a portal\nthat can transcend time itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336397,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337604,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}